      "content": "The point is, you're right, it never gets easier. You'll just be a different version of yourself, still not fitting in, still pretending to be someone you're not. The effort of existing is what makes life worth living, or so they say. But honestly, it's all just a facade. The pain and the struggle are what make life worth feeling, and if you stop feeling, then what's the point?",
